PRE-REQUISITES:

    yum install docker docker-compose git wget

PARAMS:

    JIRA VM with 172.17.8.182 - 172.17.8.182
    CONFLUENCE,PG_ADMIN,POSTGRES VM with 172.17.8.181 - 172.17.8.181
    CROWD+HTTP VM with 172.17.8.187 and accessible via ${PROXY_URL} - 172.17.8.187

    ADMIN_USER: conjir
    ADMIN_PASS: Camel0
    MEMORY: 4092m
    PROJECT NAME: pepco
    DIRECTORY CROWD: PEPDIR

USE

Before install activities create a new branch and replace PARAMS above with real values.
On hosts download already personalized instructions from your branch

    git clone https://github.com/gabrielstar/atlassian_stack.git
    git fetch
    git checkout -b pepco origin/pepco
    git pull


BASIC SET-UP

1. Set up PG_ADMIN 172.17.8.181:9999 and POSTGRES-9.6 under 172.17.8.181:64320
2. Set up Confluence stand-alone under http://172.17.8.181:8090/confluence
3  Set up JIRA stand-alone under http://172.17.8.182:8080/jira
4. Set up Crowd stand-alone under http://172.17.8.187:8095/crowd
5. Set up Apache with HTTP under http://${PROXY_URL} and Configure services under http://${PROXY_URL}/confluence, http://${PROXY_URL}/jira

ADDITIONAL

6. Confgure SSL on Apache under https://${PROXY_URL}
     Set up Confluence with reverse proxy and self-signed certificate under https://${PROXY_URL}/confluence
     Set up JIRA with reverse proxy and self-signed certificate under https://${PROXY_URL}/jira
7. Set up application links using SSL



